				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">1) It will, if the ranged attack continues to correct you for direct los you wont have to move around as much.  Yeah i might have to look up from my book once in a while to adjust, thats real player involvement for ya. Plus as long as you soe yourself there is no problem if pc interference. 
<br />

<br />
2) Your complaint about not being able to do anything else due to hitting the key the entire time is false, reference <span style="font-weight: bold">"and a lot of rangers are unaware of using F-keys to map archery to and end up not being able to type while firing. "</span> You can do other stuff if you know what you are doing.
<br />

<br />
3) Frankly aside from pulling at this level NO you dont do much aside from shoot arrows.  You can off tank, and I have but you wont do it much.  You can even MT but you wont. Because what do groups want you to do?  Sit there and shoot arrows.  I never said that I think hitting a button over and over again excites me or that it takes any skill.  As for spell casting you will rarely use your spells aside from buffing and pulling.  In fact because archery does such good damage you will try your hardest not to cast spells if it can be avoided.  Group dynamics change.  I mentiond in the previous post other ocassional times you won't just sit and shoot but obviously you didn't read it.
<br />

<br />
4) I don't visit boards much, I have been out of game due to travel recently which is the only reason I post.  I had heard a rumor that hybrids might get limited enhancements but I guess not, thanks for the info.
<br />

<br />
5) Arrows DO NOT automatically stop hitting if they are pushed into a wall.  Often times if they are herded into a corner or they are pushed into a curved wall your arrows will poof yes but in a flat wall I've not had too much trouble with this problem. As for retargeting, all a person botting would need to do is hit the assist key, turn melee auto attack off and switch to ranged. I have played this game for 3 and 1/2 years and I dislike ebayers as much as anyone who has worked a character up all the way.  Again on this point if you are being called to push it means something is seriously wrong with the raid (unless you are melee'ing).  Being called to push in single groups is rare, its not nearly as effective at interupting as chain stunning or chain mezzing although if you are without those then it is the way to go.  Lastly you dont have to worry about agro at all unless you are actively trying to keep yourself high on the agro list, sorry.
<br />

<br />
6) People do walk away from their computers in high level zones, it happens all the time.  These zones are not so dangerous that you are always at your computer in fear of a train or bad pull.  Also I never said ranged auto atack would make it viable to allow people to walk away from their computers, but during combat all they would need to do is hit auto attack, snare whenever you deem a good time is (people argue about this strangely enough), and sit back and relax until its time to retarget.  The ability to do something and the viability of doing it are two different things.
<br />

<br />
7) Leave class comparisons out of this.  Don't make stupid comments about warriors, there is much more than just hitting auto melee and the taunt button.  I think thats perhaps one of the dumbest comments i've ever heard.  It shows how little you understand the game and the classes. 
<br />

<br />
<img src="images/smiles/icon_cool.gif" alt="icon_cool.gif" border="0" /> Server side lag has been a long known problem, why would you spend 100k on a featherwood?  You know if your connection is good or bad and you should know how much lag you experience during a raid.  If you know its not going to be as good as it should be, buy one of the elemental bows with a higher delay.  Problem solved.  The featherwood does work, just not for all people, don't make statements that it doesnt work.  I've seen a friend parse his featherwood against a stonewood and guess what, it was better.  Now he may statistically be an outlier but the bow itself is working.
<br />

<br />
9) I dont remember saying anything about the origonal intentions for archery, but if archery works the way it was designed to then from the point of view of sony, whats wrong with it? (not that I agree with this statement)
<br />

<br />
10) Bachelors and Masters are also degrees, who ever said anything about having a Ph.D.  Feel glad you skipped those two, treat them as acronyms and you might have a little more trouble  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
11) When someone puts /flame on and /flame off in a post I think they are trying to say something.
<br />

<br />
Here is an idea, how about you go back to the game and earn a couple more levels and a few aa's.  Until you have "been there/done that"  you are only repeating what others have said.  As it stands you have no right to complain because you havn't experienced these problems; they dont affect you.  You shouldnt talk about things you don't know and understand.
<br />

<br />
Heres my last idea, actually read my posts!  It is clear you can cut and paste but your comprehension level seems pretty low.  Reread #3 and your response to it.
<br />

<br />
Enough said.  I won't complain if they impliment this, but I'm in no rush to get it.  Hopefully they'll increase player involvement anyway.</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
