				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-size: 11px; line-height: normal">Ok this is a bit long. 
<br />
The notion that SOE instituting an auto ranged attack will reduce player participation is imo foolish.  If a player wishes to Bot a ranger they will do it, somehow someway.  Giving the example of clicking a button and then leaving or sitting there reading a book?  Well all I can say to this is what the hell is the point in playing anyway if you are going to do this?  Its been said enough "save my fingers/keyboard ... give me the full capacity of the bow I'm using"  are valid arguments for this imo.  Not to say the Bot concern is not valid argument against, but I've seen people bot rangers before for archery and its already been happening for months.  As far as adding auto BS/kick/bash etc...  There are way more times that a person with these abilities will wish to not do them than a ranger will choose to not auto range attack.  I've been in several groups where I HAVE pulled aggro from my bow damage alone.  So I still need to pay attention and switch tact at times especially in LDoN zones where getting above the group or not being in tight quarters and getting them to leave me an open LOS is much more difficult.  
<br />

<br />
Someone posted that Rangers are an easy class to play.  What makes you think the class is so easy?  I'm not saying its the most difficult to play, but its not easy to play and have people tell you, wow, your the best ranger I've ever grouped with, or have them compliment you that the tactics your using are smart.  Its not often I get this but It does happen for me.  I would seriously doubt that you are getting the full experience (not game XP mind you) and enjoyment of what it means to be a ranger. 
<br />
Perhaps playing an enchanter is more for you where you need to pay close attentin to every little thing you do or you get pasted. Or be Warrior where you just run in and soak damage deal hits and get healed, of course I've seen dumb warriors trash an otherwise good group.
<br />

<br />
When AM hit this game and Rangers started aquiring it I saw a big rush of people to build ranger toons and level them up for this very reason, most of those increased the trash talkin about rangers.  Most of them also quit b/c they didn't know what the heck they were doing, most of the Non-Main rangers that stayed, have already been botted.  If you know what you are doing, you can bot anything, and probably will.  And so what?  What difference does this make to you?  Player interaction?  With what?  Other players?  The envirionment?  The Mobs?  POP mobs will still summon a botted ranger if it deals enough aggro ... dead bot.  
<br />

<br />
Whether or not SOE intended Archery to be the main mode of attack for rangers, that is what it has become.  Just as they never intended for bards to initially be able to twist songs,  they have figured out how to do just that, which has led to swarm kiting, which was never intended by Verant now SOE in the first place, but how many bards have trained your group, or taken your mobs, because they were swarming?
<br />

<br />
My only decision for choosing Yes give me ARA (auto Range Attack) is to let me have my full effectiveness of the weapon as it was designed.  </span><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=623266" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.digikitten.com/playhousev2/files/Ranger_lahru/smrusg2.png" border="0" /></a>
<br />
Tunare's 65th Forest Stalker
<br />
Rodcet Nife Server</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
