				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Personally, I don't care either way but I'd go along with this on one condition. On the SAME PATCH auto attack archery is introduced, every elemental bow (featherwood, driftwood, obsidianwood, and stonewood) be made no drop and/or REQUIRED LEVEL 65. In fact, since Sony has proven that they can require certain skill levels in order to equip an item (look at the staff Lcea Katta drops for proof), I think a way should be developed to require certain kill flags in order to equip an item. If you can't zone into Fire, you can't equip an Obsidianwood bow. Same goes for Air/Featherwood, Earth/Stonewood, and Water/Driftwood. Just add a line to the Featherwood/Stonewood/Driftwood that says Required flags: Rallos Zek the Warlord, Agnarr the Storm Lord and to the Obsidianwood, Required flags: Rallos Zek the Warlord, Solusek Ro.
<br />

<br />
My reasons are simple. Elemental bows represent such a sharp increase in damage potential that never before has a single item done similarly. People thought Ragebringers increased Rogue damage potential back when they were introduced? But at least Freebringer had to be quested. Going from a Thunderbolt to a Stonewood is quite the jump. With auto-attack archery, it would make Ranger "the next big thing" as far as the newest twink of the month. I've gone through that as a Rogue, I'd rather not have to do it again.
<br />

<br />
I don't see what the big deal is. With Gamepad and Nostromo N50 being viable workarounds, I think developer resources could be better used elsewhere. Fix the archery bugs that have always existed, for example. Those bugs that SoE points at as balancing measures for archery. Some folks don't want to use gamepads and that's their choice. Casters didn't want to use instaclickies to force the client to update correctly but many of them did (which forced SoE to fix the recast times on spells, which they flubbed). Using gamepads takes the human error out of archery (since a 'machine' can react a lot faster than many humans can, when programmed correctly). Besides that, after looking at <a href="http://forums.interealms.com/ranger/showthread.php?threadid=32116" target="_blank" class="postlink">Aoenla's gamepad test results</a> I think auto attack archery would increase DPS so much that it would undoubtedly cause an unprecedented uproar of 'whines' from other DPS classes. Adarien is correct in saying that archery has very few drawbacks in comparison to other damage classes. To increase its damage potential even further would tread that balance line and may even cross it.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Then again, given the way Sony basically gave spells to pure melee with no real drawbacks (my rogue can chain discs and endurance isn't even a consideration), this might be warranted. I voted yes before really thinking too much about it though.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.eqrangers.com/" target="_blank" class="postlink">[57 Outrider]</a><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=405025" target="_blank" class="postlink"> Trevawn</a> (Half Elf) ZONE: nro LFG
<br />
<a href="http://pub146.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse" target="_blank" class="postlink">[65 Deceiver]</a> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=11777" target="_blank" class="postlink">Trena</a> (Barbarian) ZONE: potranquility
<br />
<a href="http://menagerie.homepctech.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Menagerie</a>
<br />
<a href="http://pub173.ezboard.com/btorvboard" target="_blank" class="postlink">Torvonnilous</a>
<br />

